data.title: SARAWAK Definition & Meaning
data.meta_description: Sarawak definition: a state in the federation of Malaysia, on NW Borneo: formerly a British crown colony (1946–63) and British protectorate (1888–1946). About 50,000 sq. mi. (129,500 sq. km). Capital. See examples of SARAWAK used in a sentence.
